name: The Sports Bra
directions: In the back of the bar to the right
comment: This is a very safe space that is run by queer women and shows only women’s sports

name: Eventide Oyster Co
directions: In the back past the bar
comment: Unknown whether it’s for patrons only

name: Cottonwood Park
directions: Near the picnic tables
comment: All bathrooms are large shared unisex bathrooms with private stalls. Really nice actually.

name: Neptune Theatre
directions: Gendered washrooms in main lobby, gender neutral on lower level (accessible by elevator or stairs)
comment: Mainly for audience members, could be used whenever box office is open by asking box office agents for a washroom

name: Plant City X
directions: Both single stall unisex restrooms are to the right of the ordering counter. Only the first stall has a changing table, the one further back does not.
comment: To me it seems like you'd be able to get away with using the bathroom without buying anything, especially if you enter using the side door instead of the back, because your be turning directly right as soon as walking in.

name: Milk drunk
comment: I didn’t actually use it, but noticed they had a neutral bathroom

name: Pig Floyd BBQ
directions: First floor, straight and then make a slight left into the entrance
comment: Do not seem to check if you are a customer

name: Morton’s Moo
directions: Past the register and turn left

name: Max Burgers
comment: Free of charge

name: Roka Bar & Asian flavors
directions: Back in the north west corner.
comment:
This is not a public bathroom, but if you're having lunch, or dinner, you are welcome to use whichever bathroom you feel most comfortable with. 
They also have a heavily queer staff, so if there is a problem, there are plenty of people that will stand up with you!

name: Blue Sky Movement Center
directions: From the Lead/Coal exit off I25, head East on Coal ~1-2 blocks, take a right at Mulberry and the first parking lot on your right is Blue Sky Chiropractic
comment: This is a center for bodywork that is queer owned and queer and trans operated. There is a door code for patients and if you’re in a restroom emergency call or text 505-948-3773. Someone is usually there 11-5 M-F and 9-3 Saturdays.

name: Villars-Gryon
directions: From the train, walk up the stairs and into the left-most entrance. Gendered group stalls, and single handicap bathroom (must ask employee for access).
comment: Must be paying customer.

name: Lily's Snack Bar
comment: Two single stall all gender

name: Great Bear Coffee
directions: Past the pastry shelf and to the left.
comment: You have to be a customer

name: NSULA Russell Hall
directions: First floor in 24 hr computer lab
comment: Need ID for after hours entrance

name: Jacquelyn
directions: Come in through the front black door. Across from the staircase. Levered door handle on your left just past the slim table
comment: Ask if this is the Booth house

name: Vinny's Pizza
directions: By drink fountain, past ordering/pickup counter
comment: There are two single-stall, asseccible unisex restrooms.

name: Mantra Restaurant and Bar
directions: Right at the entrance, take a left into the small hallway
comment: There is a code needed to unlock the bathroom. It’s on the back of the sign near the entrance

name: CHOP Barbershop (Midtown)
street: 1318 N Monroe St # D, Tallahassee, FL 32303
directions: The restrooms are past the barber chairs.
comment: This is an inclusive place for a haircut in general, but the bathroom in the back is an extra nice touch.

name: Chihuly Museum
directions: Family restroom near the entrance and gift shop
comment: You may have to buy a ticket to get in, but if you have to it’s worth it

name: Bradford Community Church Unitarian Universalist
directions: Main floor near front door
comment: Open when services or other activities are happening. 2 restrooms available.

name: Dartmouth College McNutt Hall
directions: Enter via side of building to basement or enter on ground floor and restrooms are on second and basement levels
comment: Elevator is on right side of building by basement stairs

name: Ekohallen
directions: Right by the entrance as well as further inside
comment: Free of charge

name: Connaught Theatre
directions: From the main foyet - Gender neutral toilets to the left down a few stairs. Accessible toilet to the right through some doors and then round to the left at the back of the theatre.

name: Ramey
directions: Walk straight and then turn right at the checkouts. Keep walking straight past the pharmacy and into a hallway then turn right. Restroom is the last door.
comment: Anyone can use this restroom without notice.

name: Martin Luther King Park Basketball Court
directions: 2 Bathrooms are in the southwest corner of the park, right next to the basketball courts and behind Sausalito Pottery.

name: Eataly
directions: On the second floor where the entrance from the street is, across from registers.
comment: Two neutral restrooms.

name: Kigawa Bistro
comment: You have to be a paying customer. Sushi is fresh and big portions!

name: Target pharmacy
directions: Inside, next to the pharmacy
comment: Unisex restroom

name: Kohls
directions: Near the Customer Service / Returns Counter

name: Target FSU
directions: The restrooms are located in the back of the store near the video games and exercise equipment.

name: Agency for Healthcare Administration: Building 2
comment:
It's absolutely hypocritical and vile that a state agency responsible for ripping away trans healthcare from Floridian Medicaid recipients has this...but they do have a unisex restroom on Floor 3 of Building 2.

In the hellish circumstance that you end up having to visit this building in person, this is available. (The toilet gets clogged a lot, however.)

name: Florida State University: Rogers Building
directions: The Department of Statistics has three restrooms on different floors. The first floor one is across from their advising office, with the third and fourth floor being accessible via the elevator.
comment: Iirc, the first floor restroom has an accessibility button that can be pressed to open the door.

name: IU School of Dentistry
directions: Through lobby on the left
comment: Two "all gender" restrooms

name: At Home
directions: Back of the store, there’s men, women, and unisex bathrooms
comment: It’s a big enough store that I don’t think you’d have to “look around” much!

name: Lylah's
directions: Straight back from the entrance
comment: Breakfast joint open til 2pm

name: Loves
comment: Didn't get called "sir" and even had a moment to compare nails

name: Sidecar Home Market
directions: In the very back left of the building that is available to the public area (direct view is blocked by a small wall)
comment: Very accepting area here, they'll let you use the bathroom without issues. Cannot recall if there was a changing station here

name: Target
directions: Across the street from WalMart and next to Home Depot.
comment: One “family” bathroom and two multi-stall gendered bathrooms

name: Mutiny Radio
comment: Re: accessibility  - no stairs, however it is a small bathroom with no grab bars.

name: Georgie's Cafe
directions: In the back on the left

name: Rupert’s
directions: In the back by the kitchen area and bar area.
comment: You don’t have to pay or have act like you’re browsing. There are two restrooms for the entire restaurant (unless there’s other’s for the employees). One has a changing station, and the other does not (there is a sign on the door that says it has a changing station).

name: Hello Again Books
directions: All the way in the back down the hallway
comment: No expectations at all, community-owned store

name: Wagonhound rest area
directions: On the left hand side before the women's rolm
comment: Family rest room

name: Hacienda del Rio
directions: Directly to right of entry

name: Village of Wellington - Community Center
directions: First level and second level
comment: Public facility-all are welcome

name: Village of Wellington City Hall
directions: First level near Council Chambers
comment: Public facility-all are welcome

name: Night Lizard Brewery
directions: Right by the bar.
comment: It's a business (with nice friendly people) so you should buy something.

name: Booze 'n' tales
directions: upstairs.

name: Victoria Station
directions: Past the McDonald's, on the left. Gendered stall are 350 feet from accessible neutral stall.
comment: Free to use

name: Carver Brewing Compan
directions: In the front, around the corner to the left. Around the next corner is another to the left as well.
comment: You don’t have to pay, you don’t have to hide it. You can ask where their restrooms are and on the sign it may say ‘Ladies’ or ‘Men’ on it, but below that it says ‘& All other Genders’.

name: Free Bird
comment: It's a restaurant so I assume for paying customers only.

name: Glen Elm Library
directions: On the left, a bit past the front lobby, between the two gendered washrooms.
comment: There's a sign saying they do washroom checks every 15 min. But don't know how closely it's followed.

name: Root Down
directions: These bathrooms are gendered, however, this is a safe space. Especially the women’s bathroom

name: Sun-Ray Cinema
directions: Upstairs to the left of service counter
comment: These bathrooms are gendered, however, it is an extremely safe space and the “women’s” bathroom is twin peaks themed!!

name: The Flamingo
directions: Both at the back of the bar

name: The Walrus
directions: Two bathrooms, one next to the bar area and one toward the back of the bar.
comment: There’s always plan b and condoms in the bathrooms ✨

name: Cafe in the Square
directions: Just past the food counter
comment: Have to be a paying customer of the cafe to use it.

name: John Edwards Market
directions: Back of the store.
comment: Many staff are Jehovah’s Witnesses. Probably won’t say anything  best way is to enter through rear entrance, second right.

name: ReUse Megacenter
directions: Three quarters of the way to the back on the left side of the store.
comment: "For customers" and you have to ask for the key, but it's not always locked. It's a large thrift store, so you almost definitely don't need to buy anything to get the key. Store is located indide the mall.

name: Pittsburgh Children's Museum
directions: Third floor near water area. Several accessible, kid-friendly single stall restrooms
comment: Must pay museum admission

name: Garrett's Brewing Company
directions: Directly to the back past the bar. There is a family restroom and a unisex restroom.
comment: The restaurant is counter service, so it would probably be easy to sneak back to the bathroom without paying. The stall is really big, so seems accessible.

name: Dollar Tree
directions: Next to the pizza hut

name: Signal Convenience Store
directions: Walk straight and turn left at the sign that says "Restrooms" Then turn right and walk straight down the hall until you come to the Family Restroom.
comment: Anyone can use this restroom without being noticed. No purchase required.

name: Subway
directions: Walk straight back between the booths and ordering station.
comment: Anyone can use these restrooms.

name: Dollar General
directions: Walk straight until the aisles widen, then turn left.
comment: You do have to ask for a key but you don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Dollar General
directions: Turn right as soon as you walk in and keep walking straight.
comment: You do have to ask for a key but you don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Dollar General
directions: Head left as you enter the door and walk straight until you're in a hallway. Restrooms will be to your right.
comment: You do have to ask for a key but you don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Dollar General
directions: Turn left as you come through the door and head straight back into a hallway. Restrooms will be on your right.
comment: You do have to ask for a key but you don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Aldi
directions: Turn left as soon as you walk through the door and keep going straight passed the checkouts until you're in a hallway. Restrooms will be to your left.
comment: Anyone can use these bathrooms. These bathrooms are large and very accessible.

name: Howell County Courthouse
directions: There are 4 entrances to the courthouse. If you take the side entrance (facing Washington Avenue) the the restroom will be on your left as you walk in. If you take the front entrance (facing Main Street) then walk forward until you get to the 4 way cross and turn left. If you take the other side entrance (facing Aid Avenue) then keep walking straight until you're near the opposite entrance. If you enter the rear entrance (facing West Plains Bank, Main Street cont.) walk straight until you get to the 4 way cross, then turn right and walk towards the side entrance.
comment: It's a very nice bathroom and if you enter through the side, no one will even notice you.

name: AmStar Crossroads Convenience
directions: Head left as you walk in, then take a right behind the dividing wall.
comment: Anyone can use these restrooms, and they're kept very clean!

name: Book Nook
directions: Up the stairs and all the way to the right.
comment: Anyone can use this restroom without notice, however there is absolutely no wheelchair access.

name: Subway
directions: Take a right as you walk in and head past the cash register down a small hallway.
comment: Anyone can use these restrooms without question.

name: Subway
directions: Just keep walking straight until you see "Restrooms" sign on the wall, and they'll be to your right.
comment: Anyone can use these restrooms without being noticed.
